üñ•Ô∏è 2Ô∏è‚É£ What is Platform?

A platform means the environment or system on which a program runs ‚Äî like Windows, macOS, Linux, or Android.

Every software needs a platform to work.

üß† Types of Platform:

(1) Platform Dependent

If a program runs only on a specific operating system, it is called platform dependent.

C language is platform dependent because if you compile a C program on Windows, the compiled .exe file will not run on Linux or macOS.

Real-Life Example:
Think of a mobile charger that fits only one type of phone.
If you switch phones, you‚Äôll need a new charger.
That‚Äôs platform dependent.


(2) Platform Independent

If a program can run on any operating system, it is called platform independent.

Java is platform independent because once you write and compile a Java program, it can run on Windows, Linux, or macOS without any changes (using JVM ‚Äì Java Virtual Machine).

Real-Life Example:
Think of a USB charger that works with any phone ‚Äî Samsung, iPhone, Vivo, etc.
No need to change it ‚Äî that‚Äôs platform independent.


